"v.担保，证明 【英】 vi. 担保, 证明(guarantee the reliability of) 【考】 反义词: refuse to guarantee(拒绝担保) v. 担保; 证明 【记】vou = vow(n 誓约; v 宣誓), ch: 担保需要宣誓 【反】refuse to guarantee(拒绝担保) 【记】voice 声音，发声宣誓来担保 【相关】vow 宣誓, 发誓 vouch (v.)  early 14c., ""summon into court to prove a title,"" from Anglo-French voucher, Old French vocher ""to call, summon, invoke, claim,"" probably from Gallo-Roman *voticare, metathesis of Latin vocitare ""to call to, summon insistently,"" frequentative of Latin vocare ""to call, call upon, summon"" (see voice (n.)). Meaning ""guarantee to be true or accurate"" is first attested 1590s. Related: Vouched; vouching."
